00:14:46.192 --> 00:14:48.672
We think there is potentially immune reaction to the enzyme.

243
00:14:49.132 --> 00:14:52.472
So we went downstream, and we reasoned that if we targeted the disulfide

244
00:14:52.512 --> 00:14:56.392
reductases, the tumors would not be able to reduce cystine to cysteine.

245
00:14:56.772 --> 00:15:00.712
And because they naturally lacked this step here in transsulfuration

246
00:15:00.982 --> 00:15:03.562
in our lung tumors, they would have no source of cysteine.

247
00:15:04.812 --> 00:15:08.572
And so we did this. We knocked out both enzymes in a KRAS-driven lung

248
00:15:08.652 --> 00:15:10.972
tumor model with and without a Nrf2 mutation.

249
00:15:11.262 --> 00:15:14.672
And we were surprised to find that it only really had a moderate effect on tumor

250
00:15:14.732 --> 00:15:18.482
number, also tumor grade. And we really

251
00:15:18.512 --> 00:15:18.952
couldn't

