263
00:15:53.912 --> 00:15:57.392
So we needed to reevaluate some of our assumptions about how this metabolic pathway

264
00:15:57.432 --> 00:15:57.992
was working.

265
00:15:59.632 --> 00:16:03.512
So nutrient availability impacts metabolic vulnerabilities, and

266
00:16:03.572 --> 00:16:07.021
we do a lot of work in cell culture where we're

267
00:16:07.052 --> 00:16:10.572
giving an excess of nutrients, and we also like to look at the

268
00:16:10.612 --> 00:16:13.832
blood and think about that as physiological nutrient availability.

269
00:16:14.292 --> 00:16:18.252
But work from Isaac Murra has taught us that what's locally available to tumor in

270
00:16:18.272 --> 00:16:21.592
the interstitial fluid can be quite different from the circulation.

271
00:16:22.132 --> 00:16:22.602
And so he's

272
00:16:23.852 --> 00:16:27.412
characterized by metabolomics the nutrient

273
00:16:27.452 --> 00:16:31.012
availability of interstitial fluid and found it can be quite limiting in

274
00:16:31.052 --> 00:16:34.792
certain metabolites and have quite a lot of other ones.

275
00:16:34.892 --> 00:16:35.262
So we

276
00:16:36.812 --> 00:16:37.812
followed his example,

277
00:16:39.172 --> 00:16:41.412
and we looked at both blood and interstitial fluid.

278
00:16:42.032 --> 00:16:45.692
And so first we looked in the serum, and like what was previously reported,

279
00:16:46.112 --> 00:16:49.231
we find that in our two different lung cancer models, there's really no cysteine

280
00:16:49.252 --> 00:16:52.912
available. The redox state of the serum is very oxidizing.

281
00:16:53.292 --> 00:16:56.802
And when we look at cystine, there's about 10 to 15 micromolar,

282
00:16:57.412 --> 00:17:00.412
but it's all the cystine form, no cysteine.

283
00:17:00.432 --> 00:17:02.762
And the glutathione redox state followed the same trend.

284
00:17:03.092 --> 00:17:06.593
We found no reduced glutathione. All of the glutathione was in its

285
00:17:06.672 --> 00:17:09.853
