287
00:17:13.472 --> 00:17:17.392
experiments. Then we collected interstitial fluid from these

288
00:17:17.432 --> 00:17:20.532
models and asked what about cysteine availability locally.

289
00:17:21.972 --> 00:17:24.412
And again, sorry for the pixelation, but I think it's legible.

290
00:17:24.932 --> 00:17:28.632
So when we compared serum to lung, then to lung tumors,

291
00:17:29.092 --> 00:17:31.692
we found that normal healthy lung looked a lot like the serum.

292
00:17:31.852 --> 00:17:34.512
So there was very little cysteine present.

293
00:17:35.012 --> 00:17:38.612
It was all cystine, and the concentration looked pretty similar to the blood.

294
00:17:38.632 --> 00:17:41.392
But when we looked at the lung tumors, we found that it was flipped.

295
00:17:41.432 --> 00:17:45.372
So there was cysteine present locally in the tumors, and it was quite high,

296
00:17:45.452 --> 00:17:48.932
about 40 micromolar, with very little cystine, only about two

297
00:17:48.972 --> 00:17:52.772
micromolar. So thinking about transporter dependence,

298
00:17:53.372 --> 00:17:55.212
they're likely not taking up cystine.

299
00:17:55.242 --> 00:17:58.272
They're instead using a cysteine transporter.

300
00:17:58.352 --> 00:18:01.352
And glutathione, the redox state, followed a similar trend.

301
00:18:01.372 --> 00:18:04.672
There was quite a lot of reduced glutathione in the microenvironment, about one

302
00:18:04.732 --> 00:18:08.692
millimolar, really high levels. And the oxidized glutathione was found

303
00:18:08.712 --> 00:18:10.892
in both normal lung and the lung tumors.

304
00:18:11.392 --> 00:18:14.532
So we think this is very much changing their transporter

305
00:18:14.952 --> 00:18:18.752
dependence, their usage of cysteine, and the availability of

306
00:18:18.772 --> 00:18:21.522
reduced glutathione maybe is keeping that cysteine in its reduced

307
00:18:21.592 --> 00:18:25.252
form.So if we looked across a lot of

308
00:18:25.292 --> 00:18:29.192
different metabolites that we found in the interstitial fluid at the concentrations

309
00:18:29.232 --> 00:18:32.512
that they're present, there are a lot of amino acids, for example, that are

310
00:18:32.572 --> 00:18:36.432
somewhat similar between interstitial fluid and our cell culture media, within

311
00:18:37.092 --> 00:18:40.492
one to two times. But then there's a lot that are really different.

312
00:18:40.592 --> 00:18:44.442
